                                How often should I have dental check-ups and cleanings?
                            </span>
                        </button>
                        <p class="cs-item-p">
                            We recommend dental check-ups and cleanings every six months for most patients. However, some individuals may need more frequent visits based on their oral health needs.
                        </p>


                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <button class="cs-button">
                            <span class="cs-button-text">
                                What is the importance of fluoride treatments, and are they necessary for adults?
                            </span>
                        </button>
                        <p class="cs-item-p">
                            Fluoride treatments help strengthen tooth enamel and prevent decay. While especially important for children, adults can also benefit, particularly those at higher risk for cavities.
                        </p>
                    </li>
                    <li class="cs-faq-item">
                        <button class="cs-button">
                            <span class="cs-button-text">
                                Are dental sealants only for children, or can adults benefit from them too?
                            </span>
